{"id": "ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0", "rating": 4.1, "userRatingCount": 86, "displayName": {"text": "Ry's Poke Shack Pasadena", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pacmVtUlZTVFExYTJzMmEyTmFPRXBRYkVVM2MwRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Lets start my review of Ry's Poke Shack\n\nFirst off let's start with parking. Parking in the main plaza is limited but theres plenty of parking in the back lot behind the main plaza. For those of you who have parking anxiety youre good to go on this one.\n\nThe place is a bit small with limited seating but theres plenty of standing room outside\nWait times can be a bit deceiving the line moves rather quick but the orders stack up ended up waiting 30ish minutes after ordering to receive my food.\n\nNow on to the food. We purchased the Tusunami poke nachos with Ahi for the fish, in the firecracker style. I absolutely enjoyed  almost everything about this dish. The flavors instantly reminded me of Hawaii where I had the opportunity to enjoy Poké from the islands. As much as I wanted to stop eating I couldn't help my self devour the entire dish. The crab was delishous,  The Ahi was good and the pickles, my goodness  the pickles were so delightful. Theres a sign on the counter that says the pickles were made with love and I believe every word. The pickles had a bread and butter pickle flavor sweet and tangy.\n\nMy only gripe and its a stretch but the fried wonton were a bit too thin but over all definitely 9.7 / 10 will eat again monthly.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Lets start my review of Ry's Poke Shack\n\nFirst off let's start with parking. Parking in the main plaza is limited but theres plenty of parking in the back lot behind the main plaza. For those of you who have parking anxiety youre good to go on this one.\n\nThe place is a bit small with limited seating but theres plenty of standing room outside\nWait times can be a bit deceiving the line moves rather quick but the orders stack up ended up waiting 30ish minutes after ordering to receive my food.\n\nNow on to the food. We purchased the Tusunami poke nachos with Ahi for the fish, in the firecracker style. I absolutely enjoyed  almost everything about this dish. The flavors instantly reminded me of Hawaii where I had the opportunity to enjoy Poké from the islands. As much as I wanted to stop eating I couldn't help my self devour the entire dish. The crab was delishous,  The Ahi was good and the pickles, my goodness  the pickles were so delightful. Theres a sign on the counter that says the pickles were made with love and I believe every word. The pickles had a bread and butter pickle flavor sweet and tangy.\n\nMy only gripe and its a stretch but the fried wonton were a bit too thin but over all definitely 9.7 / 10 will eat again monthly.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "lincoln brown", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110801591438342644885/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaxV7LXeDNDPMGZfmtHTLlI9l8I5W2pxcUB5wG167xC9YE-rZ7Xw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-27T07:59:33.429077394Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pacmVtUlZTVFExYTJzMmEyTmFPRXBRYkVVM2MwRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pacmVtUlZTVFExYTJzMmEyTmFPRXBRYkVVM2MwRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2db748325e4e7:0xdd69410f82f80c3f"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKZmRHdExRVTVUYlVSUU5WSjVWWGx3VjNOVldYYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "This is the best and most authentic poké I've had on the mainland. It's full of flavor and so very fresh!\n\nI went on a Wednesday at around 3pm and there was no wait. The staff is super friendly and very welcoming.\n\nThere's plenty of dine-in seating if you want to eat there.\n\nI got the 2 choice poke bowl with ahi limu and salmon ponzu crunch and an extra scoop of crab salad. The rice was perfectly warm paired with the fresh poké.\n\nI pretty much inhaled it when I got home. It reminded me of the flavors of Hawaii. I can't wait to go back!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This is the best and most authentic poké I've had on the mainland. It's full of flavor and so very fresh!\n\nI went on a Wednesday at around 3pm and there was no wait. The staff is super friendly and very welcoming.\n\nThere's plenty of dine-in seating if you want to eat there.\n\nI got the 2 choice poke bowl with ahi limu and salmon ponzu crunch and an extra scoop of crab salad. The rice was perfectly warm paired with the fresh poké.\n\nI pretty much inhaled it when I got home. It reminded me of the flavors of Hawaii. I can't wait to go back!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Candie Brown", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104671398777024920947/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNc9d8XSjFmvwmmT5lmKM24V729_2eqZA_zSsecPBCr6hjtSBeNA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-04T23:50:59.125141335Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKZmRHdExRVTVUYlVSUU5WSjVWWGx3VjNOVldYYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKZmRHdExRVTVUYlVSUU5WSjVWWGx3VjNOVldYYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2db748325e4e7:0xdd69410f82f80c3f"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tKWlRWRXRaVEEyTTJoblpXUm9RbUkyZVc5alprRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Some of the best poke I've had. A big fan of the California style. The fish was fresh and you get some big pieces. Rice was very mushy and not appetizing and the pickles are super sour and salty. Not a fan. The poke itself is so good it really carries the rating. I would choose the tsunami nachos over a bowl.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Some of the best poke I've had. A big fan of the California style. The fish was fresh and you get some big pieces. Rice was very mushy and not appetizing and the pickles are super sour and salty. Not a fan. The poke itself is so good it really carries the rating. I would choose the tsunami nachos over a bowl.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Joann", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106645210577877151840/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4anoY7oTK22iUM4h50rHzS4WmRUJyzEAj3iK1wDDrrPwduZk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-27T03:16:49.935129530Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tKWlRWRXRaVEEyTTJoblpXUm9RbUkyZVc5alprRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tKWlRWRXRaVEEyTTJoblpXUm9RbUkyZVc5alprRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2db748325e4e7:0xdd69410f82f80c3f"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21Wck5WQnhNVU5GWkcxdVpuQkRYek5zZUhGak4zYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Wow!!  This is by far the most delicious poke shop I've ever eaten!!  You must give them a try; you won't be disappointed.  I tried out their tsunami nachos with ahi tuna w/ponzu crunch (fried garlic, ponzu onion, green onion, furikake) and I was blown away.  Their ahi tuna was so fresh and flavorful!!   I had to go back the next day to make sure it was that good, and it was!!  I made sure to get extra ponzu crunch and extra cucumber slices.  It hit the spot again.  I love it!!  The food is 5 stars 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟 and so is their friendly customer service.  Atmosphere is good as well, this was previously the spot of the Lobster Guys, located on the southwest corner of Colorado and San Gabriel Blvd.  Thank you Ry's for being here!!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Wow!!  This is by far the most delicious poke shop I've ever eaten!!  You must give them a try; you won't be disappointed.  I tried out their tsunami nachos with ahi tuna w/ponzu crunch (fried garlic, ponzu onion, green onion, furikake) and I was blown away.  Their ahi tuna was so fresh and flavorful!!   I had to go back the next day to make sure it was that good, and it was!!  I made sure to get extra ponzu crunch and extra cucumber slices.  It hit the spot again.  I love it!!  The food is 5 stars 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟 and so is their friendly customer service.  Atmosphere is good as well, this was previously the spot of the Lobster Guys, located on the southwest corner of Colorado and San Gabriel Blvd.  Thank you Ry's for being here!!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Kat N.", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104869090695460350807/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItU4ii4F4gn6LRjyzYVGcHtbSuL4Cu9_56rlsfHipLboMKJQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-01T00:03:31.328918184Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21Wck5WQnhNVU5GWkcxdVpuQkRYek5zZUhGak4zYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21Wck5WQnhNVU5GWkcxdVpuQkRYek5zZUhGak4zYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2db748325e4e7:0xdd69410f82f80c3f"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205NmMxbzJSbFpaY0hSd01rNHRjalJrU2tWU1RtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "A really nice family owned legit poke shop! There was a small line outside but it went quick. Was able to get a seat. Super good poke! Fresh and tasty! Lots of flavor!  Staff is super friendly. If your in the area and looking for good fresh poke stop by here. Super good!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "A really nice family owned legit poke shop! There was a small line outside but it went quick. Was able to get a seat. Super good poke! Fresh and tasty! Lots of flavor!  Staff is super friendly. If your in the area and looking for good fresh poke stop by here. Super good!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Farley G", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100441160866950135691/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzM1O1suRP4WYIW9ukyZr_BJn9jl-ekIESlvML_kFVQhAPqg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-19T21:09:43.022448318Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205NmMxbzJSbFpaY0hSd01rNHRjalJrU2tWU1RtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205NmMxbzJSbFpaY0hSd01rNHRjalJrU2tWU1RtYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2db748325e4e7:0xdd69410f82f80c3f"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJ5-Qlg3TbwoARPwz4gg9Bad0/photos/AWCwydgiSuj4mMZlHdXehT7Gh-GiNekW-gu3D94l4IXmH0t047RDlK6NdnBBNNwCbUsqjbGL41L_7uzdgRP8YWbAW3y38VprE9Uh-LuCDmtrGSidS7QnOFEbqsyuDOohkco62D46EhLwR2sI86wgDCJLwtPs0CIwlUrsMccdFhFy-4MuSJPAyoia2Q0H-EFyqBJMjTcWou587mSBVuYUk3KqllVSIe87lUiBfcvdGz7eoTlzTogFwRxQVyZessL8MMO78FQ6tCXSZzjTnPhO_9IMUpkCOmiKd685C-jzwHLEkNqAgDd3st5xTRR-wGWywErz8Kp_otIJ4CXylvUmWu4uUsvPnjryKxaaGlKYIxWYTU_FhVjo_xBjnrbldLbqNgDkosB2FgED1NTk5S9qSKS4Toa6tPHAGg8XdFpM1j5znbVE-eofzmqF082zy2iWDg", "widthPx": 1080, "heightPx": 1112, "authorAttributions": [{"displayName": "Ry's Poke Shack Pasadena", "uri": "https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/104304941602081046786", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLml8G1QSpb5qgmHlpQv-QxLLU8oOoZeqIguoO3aT-70iw5Cw=s100-p-k-no-mo"}], "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.c